    "Suppose that we are given a binary function \
f:{0,1}^n\\[RightArrow]{0,1}, the value of which is determined by a secret \
string s of n bits The Bernstein-Vazirani problem finds the secret bit string \
s by making queries to the oracle f. Classically, one needs n queries to the \
function f to infer the secret string s. See also Section 4.2 of the Quantum \
Workbook (2022).", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> 
